Title : Jalley Sonam
Text : {{Use Indian English|date=May 2016}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}
'''Jally Sonam''' is an [[India]]n [[trade union]]ist and politician. As of 2014 he is the president of the All Arunachal Pradesh Workers Union.<ref>''Times of India''. ''[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/guwahati/LS-polls-BJP-NCP-name-Arunachal-nominees/articleshow/31274733.cms LS polls: BJP, NCP name Arunachal nominees]''</ref><ref name="a"/> As of 2012 he served as working president of the Arunachal Pradesh branch of the [[Indian National Trade Union Congress]] and joint convenor of the North-East states for INTUC.<ref>Government of Arunachal Pradesh. ''[http://www.arunachal.gov.in/cs/-/trade-unionist-sonam-to-attend-japan-event Trade Unionist Sonam to Attend Japan Event]''</ref><ref>''Times of India''. ''[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/guwahati/intuc-wants-safety-of-ne-people-working-in-other-states/articleshow/15584416.cms INTUC wants safety of NE people working in other states]''</ref> Sonam served as chairman of the Arunachal Pradesh Building & Other Construction Workers Welfare Board (APB&OCWWB).<ref name="a">''The Sentinel''. ''[http://www.sentinelassam.com/arunachal/story.php?sec=2&subsec=7&id=181956&dtP=2014-01-31&ppr=1 Jalley Sonam joins PPA]''</ref> He was removed from this post by the Arunachal Pradesh state government on 27 January 2014, midst protests from AAPWU and INTUC.<ref name="b">''Arunachal Times''. ''[http://www.arunachaltimes.in/wordpress/2014/01/29/aapwu-intuc-oppose-replacement-of-jalley-as-apbocwwb-chairman/ AAPWU, INTUC oppose replacement of Jalley as APB&OCWWB chairman]''</ref><ref>''Business Standard''. ''[http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/arunachal-govt-s-removal-of-aapbocwwb-chairman-irks-aapwu-114012800880_1.html Arunachal govt's removal of AAPBOCWWB chairman irks AAPWU]''</ref> Two days later Sonam joined the [[People's Party of Arunachal]] (PPA).<ref name="a"/> PPA fielded Sonam as its candidate for the [[Arunachal West (Lok Sabha constituency)|Arunachal West seat]] in the [[2014 Indian general election]].<ref>''Economic Times''. ''[http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2014-03-20/news/48402367_1_arunachal-pradesh-assembly-seats-candidate PPA announces candidate for Arunachal Pradesh]''</ref>

